widgets_values: Hyper-realistic photograph of a middle-aged red-haired womanâ€™s face, tight head-and-shoulders portrait, ultra-dramatic angle: extreme side view with the camera very close, positioned low and to her right, shooting upward across her face (near-profile), with a slight Dutch tilt (15â€“20Â°) and aggressive perspective (24mm lens look). Her near eye is sharply in focus, gaze cutting sideways toward the lens, jaw set, expression intense and controlled. Ultra high-contrast lighting: single hard key light from far left at eye level, creating a razor-sharp split-lighting effect (half the face brightly lit, the other half falling into near-black), no fill, crisp shadow edge, tiny specular highlights on the lips and the lit cheek; a thin cool rim light from high back-right outlining the hair and shoulder. Deep black background with minimal haze. Natural red hair with individual strands and flyaways, realistic skin texture with pores and fine lines, subtle freckles, detailed eyelashes and eyebrows, rich blacks and controlled highlights. She holds a rigid rectangular sign vertically beside her face, close to the camera so it feels large in frame; the sign is matte black with centered, clean white bold sans-serif text reading "Z-Refiner" (exact spelling), perfectly sharp and legible; her hand grips the lower edge, fingers partially visible with hard-edged highlights. Shallow depth of field focused on the near eye and the sign text, f/2.0.
